BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:XcJpzpdIrK33UO6JqsJqP
SUMMARY:TADAIMA: I'm Home
DTSTAMP:20260326T230623Z
DTSTART:20260331T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:After more than 80 years\, a treasured collection returns “home
	” to Seattle’s Japanese American community. In 1942 dozens of traditional 
	Boys’ and Girls’ Day dolls were entrusted to Bailey Gatzert Elementary Sch
	ool by Japanese American families facing forced incarceration. Most were n
	ever reclaimed after the war. Artist Miya Sukune uses recent research in M
	OHAI’s collection\, as well as interviews with Japanese American survivors
	 and their descendants\, to create an installation called “Tadaima\,” mean
	ing “I’m home.”\n\nTADAIMA: “I’m Home!” Bringing Seattle’s Girls’ and Boys
	’ Day Dolls Home reconnects the dolls with their traditional role of prote
	cting and blessing children. It invites visitors to celebrate the resilien
	ce\, memory\, and enduring traditions of the Japanese American Community.\
	n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-03-31T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-03-31T00
LOCATION:Museum of History and Industry\, 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, Seatt
	le\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:H22ln2wNYLfDICdxBqwCd
SUMMARY:Family Story Time
DTSTAMP:20260326T230623Z
DTSTART:20260331T171500Z
DESCRIPTION:Tuesday\, March 31\, 2026\, 10:15 - 10:45am\n\nAt storytime\, k
	ids ages 0-5 and their families can enjoy stories\, songs\, and fun learni
	ng activities.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nQueen Anne Branch\n\nRoom Location: Me
	eting Room\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not required.\n\nDeta
	iled Description: Early Learning is a great way for kids ages 0-5 and thei
	r families to develop learning\, literacy\, and language skills as well as
	 community with other families.\, We read stories\, sing songs\, and have 
	engaging\, educational activities that help kids and their caregivers grow
	 together.\n\nEvent Logistics: Registration is not required but these prog
	rams are very popular and the room capacity can fill up quickly.\, Familie
	s of all ages are welcome\, though this early learning program is intended
	 for youth aged 0-5\, their caregivers and families.\, Doors to the meetin
	g room will open at 6:40 p.m. This is a flat\, stroller-friendly entrance 
	on 4th Ave W.\, The entrance to the meeting room from the Library is down 
	a flight of stairs.\, Find out more about\n\nEarly Learning & Story Time\n
	\nprograms.\n\nContact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk
	 Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommo
	dations for people with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactL
	EAP\n\nat least seven days before the event to request accommodations.\, A
	ll Library programs are free and open to the public.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6
	amcity.com/events/#/details/family-story-time/18228704/2026-03-31T00\n\nFr
	om SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/family-story-time/1822870
	4/2026-03-31T00
